registration_id no longer hard-coded in DeviceViewSetMixin

`lookup_field` was declared in `DeviceViewSetMixin` and never used. Instead the create method referred to string literal instead of this field. No the field is used. You can inherit from `DeviceViewSetMixin`, redefined the `lookup_field` and use if with your views instead of having to rewrite the `create` method yourself

Make unused arguments part of an asterisk parameter (#536)

APNs Auth Key Support (#533)

* Update to take advantage of the update to APNS2 which supports Auth
Tokens, so multiple applications can share the same Authorization Token
rather than creating a certificate for each application.

The API is unchanged, but to be more generic, the parameter to
the functions in apns.py was changed from certificate to creds.

The major change ended up being in the configuration, since FCM and
APNS went in the direction of tokens to simplify for multiple apps, and
the app configuration went in the direction of many certificates, one
for each app. So, the future API is going to get extremely cumbersome,
which will have to be addressed.

 o Removed some overly-aspirational comments

   yet.

Avoid mutating arguments in `gcm._cm_send_request`

`gcm._cm_send_request` mutates its `data` argument by using `dict.pop`.
Since this function may be called more than once from
`push_notifications.GCMDeviceQuerySet.send_message`, with same
dict as `data` argument, only the first call will receive proper
values.
